  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Using the updated ALEPH <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>V</mi><mo>−</mo><mi>A</mi></math> spectral function from τ decays, we determine the lowest spectral moments of the left-right correlator and extract dynamical information on order parameters of the QCD chiral symmetry breaking. Uncertainties associated with violations of quark-hadron duality are estimated from the data, imposing all known short-distance constraints on a resonance-based parametrization. Employing proper pinched weight functions, we obtain an accurate determination of the effective chiral couplings <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msubsup><mrow><mi>L</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">eff</mi></mrow></msubsup></math> and <math altimg="si3.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msubsup><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>8</mn></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">eff</mi></mrow></msubsup><mn>7</mn></math> and the dimension-six and -eight contributions in the Operator Product Expansion.</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">Elsevier</subfield>
